Title:
RPC Interfaces Dump (August 2018) – Windows RPC/COM Endpoint Enumeration Output

Type:
Documentation / Other (Gist data dump)

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
This gist is a large, process-by-process dump of RPC interfaces and endpoints observed on a Windows system (circa August 2018), including interface UUIDs, versions, implementing binaries (DLL/EXE paths), procedure names/ordinals, and bound endpoints (e.g., `ncalrpc`, `ncacn_np` named pipes, `ncacn_ip_tcp` ports). It effectively maps which Windows services expose which RPC servers and how they are reachable locally or remotely. The output highlights high-value services like `services.exe` (SCM), `lsass.exe` (LSA/SAMR/DPAPI/EFS), `spoolsv.exe` (Print Spooler), `rpcss`/endpoint mapper, Task Scheduler, Event Log, and others, along with their transport bindings. This is useful for attack-surface discovery, RPC research, and building or validating RPC client tooling (stubs, IDL reconstruction, fuzzing targets). Defenders can also use it to baseline expected RPC exposure and hunt for anomalous endpoints or unexpected RPC servers. It’s interesting because it consolidates a broad Windows RPC/COM landscape into a single reference artifact tied to real running processes and endpoints.

Technical Focus:
- Windows RPC interface UUIDs, versions, and procedure tables
- RPC endpoint transports: ALPC (`ncalrpc`), Named Pipes (`ncacn_np`), TCP (`ncacn_ip_tcp`)
- Service-to-binary mapping (svchost groups, DLL hosting)
- DCOM/OLE interfaces and activation infrastructure (`rpcss`, COM base)
- High-value RPC servers (LSA/SAMR/Spooler/Task Scheduler/EventLog/SCM)
- RPC attack surface enumeration and baselining

Use Cases:
- Enumerate local/remote RPC attack surface and reachable endpoints
- Identify named pipes/ports to target for RPC client development or fuzzing
- Map sensitive services (LSASS/SCM/Spooler) to their exposed RPC interfaces
- Create defensive baselines for expected RPC endpoints per host build
- Support reverse engineering by linking interface UUIDs to implementing modules

Keywords:
Windows RPC, MSRPC, DCE/RPC, interface UUID, RPC endpoint mapper, rpcrt4, rpcss, ncalrpc, ALPC, ncacn_np, named pipe, ncacn_ip_tcp, DCOM, OLE, lsass, samr, lsarpc, services.exe, spoolsv.exe, task scheduler, eventlog, svchost, attack surface enumeration